          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Preheat oven to 375\u00b0. In a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil. Season chicken generously with salt and pepper and sear, skin-side down, until golden, 4 to 5 minutes per side. Transfer chicken to a plate and pour off half the fat from skillet."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "c21c5ea0-aed5-4c46-8945-635d2e326e08",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Return skillet to medium heat and add garlic, thyme, and red pepper flakes. Cook until fragrant, 1 minute, then stir in broth, heavy cream, sun-dried tomatoes, and Parmesan and season with more salt. Bring to a simmer, then return chicken to skillet, skin-side up."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "d2c8ec7e-6e04-4826-af08-7f16459f9f7d",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Transfer skillet to oven and bake until chicken is cooked through (and juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a knife), 17 to 20 minutes."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "3a6c298a-9a28-4911-b904-85d22f7af5f0",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Garnish with basil and serve."
        }
